
- [ ] Relative Locators in **Selenium 4** provide a new way to** locate web elements based on their spatial relationships to other elements.**


#### Key Relative Locators
Selenium 4 introduces five main relative locators:

1. **above()**: Locates an element above a specified element -> preceding
2. **below()**: Finds an element below a specified element -> following-sibling
3. **toLeftOf()**: Identifies an element to the left of a specified element -> 
4. **toRightOf()**: Locates an element to the right of a specified element
5. **near()**: Finds an element within 50 pixels of a specified element ->

****import static org.openqa.selenium.support.locators.RelativeLocator.*;***
The RelativeLocator class in Selenium provides methods like with(), above(), below(), toLeftOf(), toRightOf(), and near().
If you donâ€™t use a static import, you must call them with the class name
WebElement password = driver.findElement( RelativeLocator.with(By.tagName("input")).above(By.id("login"))
);